@NODE SourceLanguages "Source languages recognized by RoboDoc:"
@PREV IndexNode
@NEXT main

   RoboDocBuilderPPC V3.0+ does NOT use source code information (but it
   does provide a good point to document the various languages that
   RoboDoc itself recognizes):
   
   Assembly   - Any assembler that uses @{B}*@{UB} or @{B};@{UB} as comment delimiters.
   C          - My personal favorite.
   BASIC      - Any dialect that recognizes REM statements.
   FORTRAN    - Any dialect that uses @{B}C@{UB} as comment delimiters.
   LaTeX      - Text Formatting language.
   TeX        - Text formatting language.
   PostScript - A printer programming language.
   
@ENDNODE


