@NODE SortMI "Sort the output:"

   Checking this MenuItem will tell RoboDoc to use its @{B}SORT@{UB}
   flag when generating documents, which will (for example), sort the 
   output Nodes of an AmigaGuide file into alphabetical order (Ascending).

   @{" Lemme Read RoboDoc's Manual " LINK "RoboDoc.doc"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE TOCMI "Add a Table of Contents to output:"

   Checking this MenuItem will tell RoboDoc to use its @{B}TOC@{UB}
   flag when generating documents.  This means that RoboDoc will add a
   Table of Contents to the generated output.  All output types except
   @{B}ASCII@{UB} don't need this flag to generate a Table of Contents,
   so it's only checked for ASCII output type (if desired).

   @{" Lemme Read RoboDoc's Manual " LINK "RoboDoc.doc"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE InternalMI "Add Internal documentation to output:"

   Checking this MenuItem will tell RoboDoc to use its @{B}INTERNAL@{UB}
   flag when generating documents.  This means that the source comments 
   with the RoboDoc Internal markers will be placed in the generated output
   as well as the Main & Header-marked comments.

   @{" Lemme Read RoboDoc's Manual " LINK "RoboDoc.doc"}

@ENDNODE


@NODE InternalOnlyMI "Use Internal documentation only:"

   Checking this MenuItem will tell RoboDoc to use its 
   @{B}INTERNALONLY@{UB} flag when generating documents.  This means that
   @{B}only@{UB} the source comments with the RoboDoc Internal markers will be
   placed in the generated output.

   @{" Lemme Read RoboDoc's Manual " LINK "RoboDoc.doc"}
   
@ENDNODE

