@NODE GenerateXRef "Make a Cross-Reference..."
@PREV Gadgets

   Specify an input & and output filename either by typing the filenames
   in the correct string gadgets or by clicking on the appropriate @{B}ASL@{UB}
   button(s).
   
   Next, decide on whether to simply generate a Cross-Reference output, or
   use a Cross-Reference list of files as the input filename.

   NOTES:  For HTML & AmigaGuide-type output, the Cross-References are
           actually links to other autodocs (if RoboDoc is working 
           correctly!).
          
   @{B}Generate XRef@{UB}      - This generates a cross-reference file.

   @{B}Use XRef list file@{UB} - This generates an entire document, using
                                 a file that contains a list of all the
                                 cross-reference files needed.
@ENDNODE

@NODE XRefListFile "Generate a Cross-Reference from a list file:"

   RoboDoc will generate a complete cross-reference output file,
   given an input filename that contains all of the cross-reference
   files that are to be used.

   See Also, @{" Single Cross-Reference file " LINK "GenerateXRef"} generation,
             @{" Lemme Read RoboDoc's Manual " LINK "RoboDoc.doc"}
   
@ENDNODE


@NODE GenerateDoc "Generate a Document..."
@PREV Gadgets

   Specify an input & and output filename either by typing the filenames
   in the correct string gadgets or by clicking on the appropriate @{B}ASL@{UB}
   button(s).

   Next, decide if you wish to change any of the PREFERENCES that're
   displayed in the @{" Menu Strip " LINK "MenuItems"}.
   
   Click on the @{B}Generate Document!@{UB} gadget to generate the document.
    
@ENDNODE

@NODE ProcessTemplate "Edit a Template File..."
@PREV Gadgets

   RoboDocBuilderPPC will use the @{" TemplatePath " LINK "ToolTypes"} ToolType
   to edit your template files.

   The Templates that come with RoboDocBuilderPPC are good examples of what
   to put in your source code.  Make sure that you keep the original 
   Templates safe!

   First, select the type of template that you wish to edit, using the 
   given radio buttons (Mutual-Exclude) then press the @{B}Edit Template Files...@{UB} 
   button.  

   Templates included with RoboDocBuilderPPC are:
  
   @{" Header   " LINK "HeaderTemplate"}
   @{" Internal " LINK "InternalTemplate"}
   @{" Main     " LINK "MainTemplate"}
   @{" Full     " LINK "FullTemplate"}

   SEE ALSO,
   
   @{" Header Keywords " LINK "HeaderKeywords"}
   @{" Source:         " LINK "SourceLanguages"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE TabSizeGadget "Modify the Tab size:"
@PREV Gadgets

   This Integer gadget allows the user to change the TabSize used by 
   RoboDocBuilderPPC in controlling RoboDoc.
   
@ENDNODE
   
@NODE DefaultsListGadget "RoboDoc.defaults file List View Gadget:"

   This ListView gadget shows the contents of the RoboDoc.defaults file 
   that RoboDoc will use to customize its output.

   See Also, @{" Edit RoboDoc.defaults... " LINK "EditDefaults"}
             @{" RoboDoc Manual           " LINK "RoboDoc.doc"} for more info.
   
@ENDNODE

@NODE "EditDefaults" "Edit RoboDoc.defaults file:"

   RoboDocBuilderPPC will use the @{" Default Editor " LINK "ToolTypes"} to change
   the contents of RoboDoc.defaults when you click on the @{B}Edit RoboDoc.defaults@{UB}
   Gadget, allowing you to change what RoboDoc will generate 
   from your source code.
    
@ENDNODE

@NODE "InFileName" "Input Source File Gadget(s):"

   Simply type in the name of your source code file into the String
   Gadget provided, or click on the ASL File Requester located to the
   right of the String Gadget & select a source code file from the
   filing system.  This file is used for the following operations:
   
     1. @{" Edit a Source File              " LINK "EditSrcFile"}
     2. @{" Generate a Documentation file   " LINK "GenerateDoc"}
     3. @{" Generate a Cross Reference file " LINK "GenerateXRef"} 
     4. @{" Generate a Cross Reference      " LINK "XRefListFile"} from a list file.
   
@ENDNODE

@NODE "OutFileName" "Output Documentation File Gadget(s):"

   Simply type in the name of your documentation file into the String
   Gadget provided, or click on the ASL File Requester located to the
   right of the String Gadget & select a file name from the
   filing system.  This file is used for the following operation:
   
     @{" Generate a Documentation file " LINK "GenerateDoc"}
   
@ENDNODE

@NODE "XRefFileName" "Cross-Reference File Gadget(s):"

   Simply type in the name of your cross-reference file into the String
   Gadget provided, or click on the ASL File Requester located to the
   right of the String Gadget & select a file name from the
   filing system.  This file is used for the following operations:
   
     1. @{" Generate a Cross Reference file " LINK "GenerateXRef"} 
     2. @{" Generate a Cross Reference      " LINK "XRefListFile"} from a list file.
   
@ENDNODE

@NODE ProgramOperations "Program Operations:"
@PREV main

   RoboDocBuilderPPC will perform the following operations, once you've
   set up the GUI correctly:
   
   1. @{" Edit a Source File              " LINK "EditSrcFile"}
   2. @{" Generate a Documentation file   " LINK "GenerateDoc"}
   3. @{" Generate a Cross Reference file " LINK "GenerateXRef"} 
   4. @{" Generate a Cross Reference      " LINK "XRefListFile"} from a list file.
   5. @{" Edit Template files             " LINK "ProcessTemplate"}
   6. @{" Edit the RoboDoc.defaults file  " LINK "EditDefaults"}
        
@ENDNODE

@NODE EditSrcFile "Edit a Source File..."
@PREV Gadgets

   Either type in an Input File name to the Input File string gadget or
   press the @{B}ASL@{UB} button in order to select a file from the filing
   system.  Pressing @{B}Edit a Source File...@{UB} will then invoke the @{B}Default Editor@{UB}
   with the supplied filename.

   RoboDocBuilderPPC will use the @{" DefaultEditor " LINK "ToolTypes"} ToolType on
   the Input File name you gave to edit your source file.

   For what to put in your source files, in order to use RoboDoc,
   see the @{" RoboDoc Manual " LINK "RoboDoc.doc"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE GeneralInfo "RoboDocBuilderPPC General Information:"
@PREV main
@NEXT ProgramOperations

   RoboDocBuilderPPC is a Graphical User Interface (GUI) for the 
   RoboDoc (c) (V3.0j) program written by:

   @{" Maverick Software Development " LINK "RoboDoc Info"},

   In general, I hate to read documentation in order to figure out how
   to use someone else's program, this is the primary motivation for
   creating this GUI.  RoboDocBuilderPPC should eliminate the need to read
   RoboDoc's documentation, insofar as determining how to make it work
   is concerned.  What it does & why it was created still mandate the
   need for reading the documentation of RoboDoc (c).

   @{" Lemme Read RoboDoc's Manual " LINK "RoboDoc.doc"}

   @{" RoboDocBuilderPPC Requirements " LINK "Requirements"}   

   SEE ALSO, @{" Index " LINK "IndexNode"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements" "RoboDocBuilder Requirements:"

   You need the following in order to use @{B}RoboDocBuilderPPC@{UB}:
   
      AmigaOne PowerPC & AmigaOS4.

      RoboDocBuilderPPC      -- The Main Program
      RoboDocBuilderPPC.info -- The Program Icon (See @{" ToolTypes " LINK "ToolTypes"})
   
   You need the following in order to use @{B}RoboDocBuilder@{UB}:

      Amiga OS3.9+           -- (For MultiView). 

      RoboDocBuilder         -- The Main Program
      RoboDocBuilder.info    -- The Program Icon (See @{" ToolTypes " LINK "ToolTypes"})

   Common to both Platforms:

      Helvetica font (13 pts)
      
      MultiView              -- Everyone should have a copy of this!

      RoboDocBuilder.guide   -- This Help file

      RoboDoc                -- Helper program (V3.0j)

      RoboDoc.defaults       -- Included in the Distribution
      RoboDocTemplates (dir) -- Not really necessary

@ENDNODE

@NODE HeaderTemplate "Header Template contents:"
@PREV ProcessTemplate
@NEXT main

  This Template is for documentation that you want the user to see 
  concerning functions (like those for a shared library).
  
/****h* $MODULE/$FUNC $VERSION *******************
*
* NAME     $NAME
*
* SYNOPSIS $SYNOPSIS
*
* FUNCTION $FUNCTION
*
* INPUTS   $INPUTS
*
* RESULT   $RESULT
*
* EXAMPLE  $EXAMPLE
*
* NOTES    $NOTES
*
* BUGS     $BUGS
*
* SEE ALSO $SEEALSO
*
* ------------------------------------------------------
* CREATION DATE $CREATIONDATE
*
* MODIFICATION HISTORY $MODHISTORY
*
*********************************************************
*
*/
 
@ENDNODE

